# __ALCHEMIQ_ROOT__

A uv-workspace monorepo scaffolded with `alchemiq init --monorepo`. Each service
under `services/` is independent and layered (`domain -> repositories -> services ->
use_cases -> adapters`); shared event contracts live in `packages/shared`.

## Run

```bash
uv sync --all-packages
cp .env.example .env                       # fill in credentials if needed
docker compose up -d                       # infrastructure  # alchemiq:if docker
# per service, from the workspace root:
cd services/<name>
uv run --env-file ../../.env alchemiq makemigrations -m init
uv run --env-file ../../.env alchemiq migrate
uv run --env-file ../../.env uvicorn <module>.app:app --reload    # FastAPI dev server  # alchemiq:if fastapi
uv run --env-file ../../.env faststream run <module>.broker:app   # broker consumer  # alchemiq:if faststream
```

Nothing loads `.env` implicitly - the `uv run --env-file ../../.env` prefix
injects the workspace-root `.env` and runs each command inside the workspace
venv (installed CLIs such as `alchemiq` are not on your PATH otherwise).

# alchemiq:block postgres
Each Postgres-backed service owns a database named after its module;
`docker/postgres-init.sh` creates them on the postgres container's first boot
(delete the `postgres-data` volume to re-run it).
# alchemiq:endblock

## Test

```bash
uv run pytest services/<name>/tests
```
